Buba ' s Palm sees no prices problem from weak mark . Bundesbank council member Guntram Palm said on Tuesday that the Bundesbank did not see current foreign exchange levels as posing an inflationary danger for Germany . " The current currency rate levels pose no dangers for price stability , " he told Reuters in an interview . " Momentarily inflation is not plaguing us . " He also said that he saw no reason for the Bundesbank to change interest rates for the time being . " There are no factors that would prompt the Bundesbank to veer from its steady hand policy , " he said , adding that the Bundesbank ' s credibility and steadfastness in such issues was one of its biggest assets . " With us , you know where you ' re at , " he said . - - Svea Herbst - Bayliss , Frankfurt Newsroom + 49 69 756525 
